        <updateDate>2021-10-28T15:03:56Z</updateDate>
        <text>
          <![CDATA[ <p><b>Environmental Health Workforce Act of 2021</b></p> <p>This bill requires the Department of Health and Human Services (HHS) to carry out certain activities related to the environmental-health workforce. It also requires the Government Accountability Office to report on state-based practices for training and credentialing environmental-health workers.</p> <p>Specifically, HHS must develop model standards and guidelines for credentialing environmental-health workers and a plan to ensure its programs and activities meet the future needs of the environmental-health workforce.</p> <p>The bill also specifies that environmental-health workers are eligible for public-service loan forgiveness.</p>]]>
        </text>
      </summary>
